message.content: One of the most significant events that happened in Bulgaria in the past 100 years is the fall of communism and the subsequent transition to democracy. This event occurred in 1989-1990, marking the end of the communist regime that had been in power since 1944. The fall of communism brought about significant political, economic, and social changes in Bulgaria, including the establishment of a multi-party system, market-oriented reforms, and integration into the European Union. This event had a profound impact on the country's trajectory and shaped its modern history.
